\pard\plain\sa340\sl-263\slmult0\wrapdefault\s24\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\cgrid\f0\b0\i0\scaps0\strike0\fs17\afs17\ul0
{\cs18\lang1033\langfe1033\b0\i0\scaps0\strike0\cf1\expndtw0\charscalex100\dn0\fs17\afs17\ul0 Expected utility theory, is
 entirely about the rules of rationality that should govern decision utilities it has nothing at all to say about hedonic
 experiences. Of course, the two concepts of utility will coincide if people want what they will enjoy, and enjoy what they
 chose forthemselves\'97and this assumption of coincidence is implicit in the general idea that economic agents are rational.}
\par
\pard\plain\sa340\sl-263\slmult0\wrapdefault\s24\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\cgrid\f0\b0\i0\scaps0\strike0\fs17\afs17\ul0
{\cs18\lang1033\langfe1033\b0\i0\scaps0\strike0\cf1\expndtw0\charscalex100\dn0\fs17\afs17\ul0 Rational agents are expected
 to know theirtastes, both present and future, and they are supposed to make good decisions that will maximize these interests.}
\par
\pard\plain\sa340\sl-263\slmult0\wrapdefault\s24\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\cgrid\f0\b0\i0\scaps0\strike0\fs17\afs17\ul0
{\cs18\lang1033\langfe1033\b0\i0\scaps0\strike0\cf1\expndtw0\charscalex100\dn0\fs17\afs17\ul0 What we learn from the past
 is to maximize the qualities of ourfuture memories, not necessarily of ourfuture experience.}
\par
\pard\plain\sa340\sl-263\slmult0\wrapdefault\s24\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\cgrid\f0\b0\i0\scaps0\strike0\fs17\afs17\ul0
{\cs18\lang1033\langfe1033\b0\i0\scaps0\strike0\cf1\expndtw0\charscalex100\dn0\fs17\afs17\ul0 Decisions that do not produce
 the best possible experience and erroneous forecasts of future feelings\'97both are bad news for believers in the rationality
 of choice. We cannot fully trust our preferences to reflect our interests, even if they are based on personal experience,
 and even if the memory of that experience was laid down within the last quarterof an hour!}
\par
\pard\plain\sa340\sl-263\slmult0\wrapdefault\s24\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\cgrid\f0\b0\i0\scaps0\strike0\fs17\afs17\ul0
{\cs18\lang1033\langfe1033\b0\i0\scaps0\strike0\cf1\expndtw0\charscalex100\dn0\fs17\afs17\ul0 Tastes and decisions are shaped
 by memories, and the memories can be wrong.}
\par
\pard\plain\sa340\sl-263\slmult0\wrapdefault\s24\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\cgrid\f0\b0\i0\scaps0\strike0\fs17\afs17\ul0
{\cs18\lang1033\langfe1033\b0\i0\scaps0\strike0\cf1\expndtw0\charscalex100\dn0\fs17\afs17\ul0 An inconsistency is built into
 the design of our minds. We have strong preferences about the duration of our experiences of pain and pleasure. We want
 pain to be brief and pleasure to last. But our memory, a function of System 1, has evolved to represent the most intense
 moment of an episode of pain or pleasure (the peak) and the feelings when the episode was at its end. A memory that neglects
 duration will not serve our preference for long pleasure and short pains.}
\par
\pard\plain\li240\sa340\sl-263\slmult0\wrapdefault\s24\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\cgrid\f0\b0\i0\scaps0\strike0\fs17\afs17\ul0
{\cs18\lang1033\langfe1033\b0\i\scaps0\strike0\cf1\expndtw0\charscalex100\dn0\fs17\afs17\ul0 "You are thinking of your failed
 marriage entirely from the perspective of the remembering self. A divorce is like a symphony with a screeching sound at
 the end\'97the fact that it ended badly does not mean it was all bad."}
\par
\pard\plain\sa360\sl-263\slmult0\wrapdefault\s24\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\cgrid\f0\b0\i0\scaps0\strike0\fs17\afs17\ul0
{\cs18\lang1033\langfe1033\b0\i0\scaps0\strike0\cf1\expndtw0\charscalex100\dn0\fs17\afs17\ul0 The experience of a moment
 or an episode is not easily represented by a single happiness value. There are many variants of positive feelings, including
 love, and joy. Negative emotions also come in many varieties, including anger and loneliness.}
\par
\pard\plain\sa360\sl-263\slmult0\wrapdefault\s24\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\cgrid\f0\b0\i0\scaps0\strike0\fs17\afs17\ul0
{\cs18\lang1033\langfe1033\b0\i0\scaps0\strike0\cf1\expndtw0\charscalex100\dn0\fs17\afs17\ul0 Although positive and negative
 emotions exist at the same time, it is possible to classify most moments of life as ultimately positive or negative}
\par
\pard\plain\sa360\sl-263\slmult0\wrapdefault\s24\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\cgrid\f0\b0\i0\scaps0\strike0\fs17\afs17\ul0
{\cs18\lang1033\langfe1033\b0\i0\scaps0\strike0\cf1\expndtw0\charscalex100\dn0\fs17\afs17\ul0 An individual\'92s mood at
 any moment depends on hertemperament and overall happiness, but emotional well-being also fluctuates considerably overthe
 day and the week. The mood of the moment depends primarily on the current situation.}
\par
\pard\plain\sa80\sl-263\slmult0\wrapdefault\s24\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\cgrid\f0\b0\i0\scaps0\strike0\fs17\afs17\ul0
{\cs18\lang1033\langfe1033\b\i0\scaps0\strike0\cf1\expndtw0\charscalex100\dn0\fs17\afs17\ul0 Well Being}
\par
\pard\plain\sa360\sl-263\slmult0\wrapdefault\s24\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\cgrid\f0\b0\i0\scaps0\strike0\fs17\afs17\ul0
{\cs18\lang1033\langfe1033\b0\i0\scaps0\strike0\cf1\expndtw0\charscalex100\dn0\fs17\afs17\ul0 The goals that people set for
 themselves are so important to what they do and how they feel about it that an exclusive focus on experienced well-being
 is not tenable.}
\par
\pard\plain\sa360\sl-263\slmult0\wrapdefault\s24\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\cgrid\f0\b0\i0\scaps0\strike0\fs17\afs17\ul0
{\cs18\lang1033\langfe1033\b0\i0\scaps0\strike0\cf1\expndtw0\charscalex100\dn0\fs17\afs17\ul0 We cannot hold a concept of
 well-being that ignores what people want.}
\par
\pard\plain\sa360\sl-263\slmult0\wrapdefault\s24\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\cgrid\f0\b0\i0\scaps0\strike0\fs17\afs17\ul0
{\cs18\lang1033\langfe1033\b0\i0\scaps0\strike0\cf1\expndtw0\charscalex100\dn0\fs17\afs17\ul0 On the other hand, it is also
 true that a concept of well-being that ignores how people feel as they live and focuses only on how they feel when they
 think about their life is also untenable.}
\par
\pard\plain\sa360\sl-263\slmult0\wrapdefault\s24\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\cgrid\f0\b0\i0\scaps0\strike0\fs17\afs17\ul0
{\cs18\lang1033\langfe1033\b0\i0\scaps0\strike0\cf1\expndtw0\charscalex100\dn0\fs17\afs17\ul0 We must accept the complexities
 of a hybrid view, in which the well-being of both selves is considered.}
\par
